00:00:12.800 --> 00:00:16.789
Artist Guy Laramee makes hand carved landscapes
out of books.

00:00:16.789 --> 00:00:22.800
He says mountains of disused knowledge return
to what they really are, mountains.

00:00:22.800 --> 00:00:30.369
Some of his projects include Han Shan, The
Cave, The Great Wall, and Adieu from an Encyclopedia

00:00:30.369 --> 00:00:31.650
Britannica set.

00:00:31.650 --> 00:00:36.640
Eric Hart built a replica of the Game of Thrones
chest given to Daenerys in season one.

00:00:36.640 --> 00:00:42.050
There are step by step instructions on what
he did throughout the process and he condensed

00:00:42.050 --> 00:00:46.670
months of work into a seven minute video showcasing
his creation.

00:00:46.670 --> 00:00:51.739
Sculptor Liu Xue created these hybrid human
and animal sculptures.

00:00:51.739 --> 00:00:56.210
Each piece features a human head and some
sort of animal appendage and they explore

00:00:56.210 --> 00:01:04.790
the ideas of physical beauty like this man
and pig, woman and a chicken, man and dog,

00:01:04.790 --> 00:01:06.610
and this man horse.

00:01:06.610 --> 00:01:12.680
Professional origami artist Sipho Mabona intends
to build a life-sized elephant to prove that

00:01:12.680 --> 00:01:16.770
a simple piece of paper can be transformed
into anything imaginable.

00:01:16.770 --> 00:01:21.070
With the help of 3 assistants the giant paper
elephant will be made out of a sheet measuring

00:01:21.070 --> 00:01:27.180
15 by 15 meters and the final project will
stand over 3 meters tall.

00:01:27.180 --> 00:01:28.180
Draw it

00:01:28.180 --> 00:01:33.210
Qwerty is a project by artist Pablo Gamboa
Santos that superimposes typed letters of

00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:35.390
an old typewriter to create landscapes.

00:01:35.390 --> 00:01:42.310
He has more than 300 creations and they make
up a 60 meter long mural of some simple designs

00:01:42.310 --> 00:01:44.330
and some that are more intricate.

00:01:44.330 --> 00:01:49.750
Jaume Montserrat has an unraveling animal
series called Emptyland that combines different

00:01:49.750 --> 00:01:58.020
species intertwined like this owl and kangaroo,
tiger and cheetah, penguin and rabbit, bear

00:01:58.020 --> 00:02:01.049
and fox, and zebra snake.

00:02:01.049 --> 00:02:18.110
And now for the hyper realistic pencil drawings
of Diego Fazio...

00:02:18.110 --> 00:02:22.779
SpY creates humorous and thought provoking
street art that he says "are filled with equal

00:02:22.779 --> 00:02:25.459
parts of irony and positive humor."

00:02:25.459 --> 00:02:31.109
His project "cameras" involved installing
150 fake cameras on a building facade with

00:02:31.109 --> 00:02:34.379
the intention of watching over nothing.

00:02:34.379 --> 00:02:35.379
